## {#pcr-comparison-slide data-menu-title="PCR vs OLS comparison"}

[OLS vs PCR: train and test performance]{.slide-title}

<hr>

::: {#83dfc9f3 .cell execution_count=13}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
                       Model  Parameters  Train R²  Test MSE
OLS  (3 predictors: x, y, z)           3     0.944     2.112
      PCR  (M = 1 component)           1     0.944     2.095
     PCR  (M = 2 components)           2     0.944     2.110
```
:::
:::


. . .

<br>

::: {.body-text-s}
- **Train R²**: OLS can slightly overfit by spreading coefficients across 3 correlated predictors
- **Test MSE**: PCR with just 1 component achieves nearly the same test MSE as OLS — confirming that almost all predictive signal lives in PC1
:::

