:::

::: {.body-text-s}
1. The optimal $M$ is 8 — retaining 8 component(s) gives the best out-of-sample prediction accuracy.

2. When $M = p$, the $p$ PC scores span exactly the same space as the $p$ original predictors — PCA is a rotation, not a reduction. So PCR at $M = p$ is **identical to OLS**, and their CV-MSEs are equal.
:::

